# CID-PDF-API — single backend (do not fragment)

## Where the pipeline lives

**`pdf-backend`** (Render: CID-PDF-API, e.g. `cid-pdf-api.onrender.com`) is the **only** service that runs:

- Operator UI: `/operator`, dashboard, segment switcher, `/operator/today/*`
- S4 extraction review (queue + APIs + prompts wired from `src/`)
- S5 packet builder
- S6 bind flow + BoldSign webhooks + policy creation
- Shared Postgres schema; all segments distinguished by **`segment`** on submissions/quotes

**Do not** add or push operator routes, dashboard code, extraction review server code, packet builder server code, or bind flow server code into **`plumber-pdf-backend`**, **`roofing-pdf-backend`**, **`hvac-pdf-backend`**, or any other segment repo.

## What segment-specific repos are for

| In segment repo (e.g. `plumber-pdf-backend`) | Allowed |
|-----------------------------------------------|--------|
| **`Netlify/`** (or publish dir) — static landing, `fetch` to the **CID-PDF-API** `POST /submit-quote` | ✅ |
| Segment **HTML/CSS** + client-side form mapping for intake | ✅ |
| **CID_HomeBase** submodule + SUPP/ACORD assets for that segment | ✅ |
| Duplicating **operator / S4 / S5 / S6** backend code | ❌ |

Intake forms **POST to the same API host** (CID-PDF-API) with `segment: "plumber"` | `"roofer"` | etc. — not a separate operator stack per segment repo.

## Segment switcher and operator features

Commits for operator dashboard, segment filtering, S4–S6 behavior: **`pdf-backend` only** (`main`).

## Docs

- Canonical docs may live in `~/GitHub/CID-docs/` (outside repos). See repo `DOCUMENTATION.md`.
